articles.author: Jeff Foust
articles.title: Nozzle erosion blamed for Vega C launch failure - SpaceNews
articles.description: Europe plans to return the Vega C rocket to flight by the end of the year after concluding an eroded nozzle component caused a failure last December.
articles.content:
WASHINGTON Europe plans to return the Vega C rocket to flight by the end of the year after concluding an eroded nozzle component caused the failure of its previous launch last December.
